A 12-year-old girl lost her life after drowning at the Nkwe pleasure resort in Pretoria East on Monday. This is according to SAPS spokesperson Lieutenant Kay Makhubela. The girl jumped into the water at the resort and when she did not resurface, her sister tried to help her. However, when she also did not surface, a third family member jumped into the water to rescue them. The girl was certified dead after being pulled from the water. Her sister survived. The resort management had not released a statement yet, but told Rekord that they are saddened by the death. Read original story on rekordeast.co.za